well, author of &quot;But What About Socialization? Answering the Perpetual Home Schooling Question: A Review of the Literature,? has researched 24 studies on the socialization of homeschoolers, according to Bristol Herald Courier. &#10;&quot;It?s a non-issue today,&quot; said McDowell, who earned Ph.D. in educational leadership from Vanderbilt University. &quot;All the research shows children are doing well.&quot; &#10;the reality is that home educators have to say NO to all the socialization!! There is too much of it, you can not get the education done. That is the truth. &#10;Home educators are finding that when they get a skeptical MP to visit them they are shocked at what they see. &#10;Shocked in the sense that the cloud of prejudice is removed."/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1007" language="en" documentId="1017" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="MidlandsStewart" date="07 November 2009 11:58am" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6753647" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="5" thumbsDown="0" origId="1017" notes="" title="Ridiculous rules for home schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="22"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="23" end="90"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="91" end="200"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="201" end="258"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="259" end="276"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="277" end="514"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="515" end="677"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="67" sofa="1" begin="678" end="835"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="71" sofa="1" begin="836" end="946"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="75" sofa="1" begin="947" end="1007"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59 63 67 71 75"/></xmi:XMI>